cg3
------------------------------------------
Tools for the 3rd edition of the Constraint Grammar formalism

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.3.6-1
  libcg3-devel-1.3.9-1bl1
  libcg3_1-1.3.9-1bl1
  libgcc1-11.3.0-1
  libicu70-70.1-1
  libstdc++6-11.3.0-1
  libtcmalloc4-2.10-1bl1
  perl_base-5.32.1-2
  pkg-config-1.9.3-1
  python39-3.9.10-1
  python39-cg3-1.3.9-1bl1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.39-1
  cmake-3.23.2-1
  cygport-0.35.4-1
  gcc-core-11.3.0-1
  gcc-g++-11.3.0-1
  libicu-devel-70.1-1
  libtcmalloc-devel-2.10-1bl1
  ninja-1.11.0-1
  python39-3.9.10-1
  python39-devel-3.9.10-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/GrammarSoft/cg3

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/GrammarSoft/cg3/archive/refs/tags/v1.3.9.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack cg3-1.3.9-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./cg3-1.3.9-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/cg3-1.3.9-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/cg3-1.3.9-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libcg3_1-1.3.9-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libcg3-devel-1.3.9-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/python39-cg3-1.3.9-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

